<!-- Val -->
	<section xml:id="ref.declarations.val">
		<title><code>val</code>:  Bind Value</title>
		<section xml:id="ref.declarations.val.body">
			<para>
				The declaration <code><ind>val</ind></code> <replaceable>x</replaceable> <code>=</code> <replaceable>G</replaceable>, followed by expression <replaceable>F</replaceable>, is a different way of writing the expression <replaceable>F</replaceable> <code>&lt;</code><replaceable>x</replaceable><code>&lt;</code> <replaceable>G</replaceable>.
				Thus, <code>val</code> shares all of the behavior of the <link linkend="ref.combinators.pruning"><ind>pruning</ind> combinator</link>.
			</para>
		</section>
		
		<section xml:id="ref.declarations.val.syntax">
	  <title>Syntax</title>
	  <para>
